Description: Rim, handle and shoulder sherd of Corinthian, possibly black-figured, globular aryballos; much worn; on top of mouth, petals; dots around edge of rim; two chevrons between horizontals on outside of handle, sides glazed; slight traces of glaze on shoulder.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 218, no. 8)
Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 59, no. A26)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.299) (phase 3)
